"A.P.238/4/9/11:30": "This is the end of the forest area, huh. Looks like we can take a break here."
"Watching you fight though, I don't think you need one."
"Every time I see you, you seem to get more refined. Honestly, I'm pretty jealous of how fast you've grown."
"Movement like that... I heard it's the result of relentless training that's been repeated over and over again."
"I don't know how much you can do that in such a short time..."
"Oh, sorry. It looked like I was blaming you or something."
"It's not bad to be strong. As long as you don't go over your limit, it's definitely a good thing."
"Hahahaha! Hey there, participants! I hope you're enjoying yourselves!"
"Ugh, I want to take part too..."
"Hm... is someone calling?"
"Please disconnect the communication line! Ahem... time to report the current standing!"
"...Right now, the pair in the lead is the pair of <%me> and the Hunter Sara!"
"What? Wow! No way, something that needs my power?! Maria even asked for me personally!"
"It seems that Ohza the Hunter and the Force Marlu are trying their best as well!"
"Okay, I got it! On my way!"
"Nonetheless, it's neck-and-neck! The Battle Tournament is a fierce struggle! The tide could turn at any moment!"
"I found something more fun, Clarissa! Sortie, quickly!"
"The second half of the game begins here, so... Aw, come on!"
"Claris Claes, you're supposed to be putting on this event, don't disappear on me!"
"Well, it did look like fun! The second half of the game begins here, so we expect you to do your best! That's all!"
"...Seems like that old hag has left. I can stick around, then..."
"Huh? Oh, sorry. Forget you heard that."
"Anyway, it looks like we can keep our lead by carrying on as we are."
